Anaerobic manipulations were performed in an anaerobic chamber (Coy Laboratories, Ann Arbor, MI, USA) with an atmosphere of 5% H2 in N2. X-band EPR measurements were performed using a Bruker E500 ELEXSYS continuous-wave spectrometer with the Bruker dual-mode cavity (ER4116DM) or a standard cavity (ER4102ST) and an Oxford Instruments helium-flow cryostat (ESR 910). Microwave frequencies were measured with a Hewlett–Packard frequency counter (HP5352B), and the field control was calibrated with a Bruker NMR field probe (ER035M). The spectra were simulated on the basis of a spin-Hamiltonian description of the electronic ground state: 1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
